reviews.positive_text: We booked two rooms that are adjacent to each other but not connecting and value for money was great - it's cheap but still clean enough. We always had parking in the basement and is included in the pricing. We just had to get our ticket stamped.
reviews.negative_text:
Breakfast very mediocre - It's 29RM per person, I understand that there won't be a lot of choice, however, I would still expect that the food would taste good, but it wasn't. Food bland or too salty, and do not look very appetizing. Even the porridge lacked the necessary condiments. Also breakfast starts at 7am.

Pool - they ONLY open at 10AM! I wish this was made very clear before we booked on the site. When you are travelling with kids, they obviously go to the pool and our kids are early risers (most kids are!) and so we didn't have much to do before 10AM and a lot of the shops and cafes also open at 10AM... 

Aircon was so cold in the room, unbearably so. The two nights I stayed there - I had to turn it off. 

Basically it's a hotel that stopped trying. Guards at the entrance of the hotel play on their phone, don't even try to say hello to you. When you want to offload things from your car, they don't offer to give you a temporary parking even though they can clearly see you with kids... experience was really unpleasant that we considered just leaving after the first night.
